Definition: make or coin into a word or accept a new word into the lexicon of a language
Example: The concept expressed by German `Gemuetlichkeit' is not lexicalized in English
Synonyms: noun, process, lexicalization, lexicalise, formulate, make, or, coin, into, a, word, accept, new, the, lexicon, of, language, The, concept, expressed, by, German, Gemuetlichkeit, is, not, lexicalized, in, English
